Iavan Pijoos, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Lydenburg - Eighteen people were injured after a taxi crashed into a tractor under a railway bridge in Lydenburg, Mpumalanga on Wednesday afternoon, paramedics said.Netcare911 spokesperson Chris Botha said two people were critically injured.&nbsp;The remainder sustained serious to minor injuries.&nbsp;They were transported to hospital.&nbsp;The incident happened at around 16:45.&nbsp;This accident comes a week after 20 people were killed after a minibus crashed into a truck on the R25 near Verena in Mpumalanga. Eighteen of them were pupils.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.